the equivalence of reducing transitionlanguages and deterministic languages.wthe class of reducing transition languagesintroduced by eickel, paul, bauer, and samelson was shown by morris to be a proper superclass of thesimple precedence languages.  in this paper this result is extended, showing that, in fact, the first classis equivalent to the class of deterministic context free languages.cacm september, schkolnick, m..kreducing transition languages, syntax controlledgenerators, deterministic context-free grammars.c. .ca jb january ,   : am